This paper deals with the problem of securing the privacy of a subscriber's long-term identity in the 5G network. This problem falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The proposed solution is based on encryption techniques, which also falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses mutual authentication and key agreement protocols, which can be categorized under cryptography (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
